.TH DESGRANA 1 "May 2026" "desgrana 1.6.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
desgrana \- extract channels from Behringer Wing multitrack WAV recordings
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B desgrana
\fI<session-dir>\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B desgrana
extracts individual mono or stereo tracks from the interleaved multichannel
WAV files produced by a Behringer Wing (or X\-Live) console.
.PP
It reads session metadata from \fISE_LOG.BIN\fR, channel names and stereo
pairs from a Wing snapshot (\fI.snap\fR), skips silent channels automatically,
and exports session markers as cue chunks in every output WAV, plus CSV and
Standard MIDI File (type 0) exports.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output \fI<path>\fR
Output directory (default: \fI<session-dir>_extract/\fR).
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-prefix \fI<string>\fR
Prefix for output filenames.
.TP
.B \-\-snap \fI<file>\fR
Wing snapshot (.snap) for stereo pairs and channel names.
Auto-detected if present in the session directory.
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-stereo \fI<pairs>\fR
Stereo pairs, e.g. \fI1:2,3:4\fR. Overrides pairs from \-\-snap.
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-info
Show session info only, without extracting.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display help and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B desgrana /media/SD/X_LIVE/4B5C62B0
Extract all channels from the session directory.
.TP
.B desgrana /media/SD/X_LIVE/4B5C62B0 \-\-info
Show session metadata without extracting.
.TP
.B desgrana /media/SD/X_LIVE/4B5C62B0 \-\-snap ~/MyShow.snap \-o ~/Desktop/extract
Extract using a named snapshot file, writing to a custom output path.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I <session-dir>/SE_LOG.BIN
Session metadata: channel count, sample rate, take sizes, markers.
.TP
.I <session-dir>/*.snap
Wing snapshot (optional): channel names, stereo pairs.
.TP
.I <session-dir>/00000001.WAV, 00000002.WAV, \&...
Interleaved multichannel WAV takes (32-bit PCM, max ~4 GB each).
